Last season’s beaten finalists Arsenal begin their Europa League campaign this term, with a trip to Germany to face Frankfurt. The Gunners lost 4-1 to Chelsea in Baku, failing to qualify for the Champions League. Frankfurt, however, lost in the semi-finals to the Blues and will be seeking to go a step further this year. Kick off is 5.55pm West African time. Thursday, September 19
